<h3 id="considerations">Considerations:</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Pure CSS/HTML?</li>
  <li>Window size change?</li>
  <li>Speed/bugginess?</li>
  <li>Handling of long/frequent Sidenotes?</li>
  <li>Option to make only footnote/only sidenote/both?</li>
  <li>Ease of access in markdown</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="options">Options:</h3>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.gwern.net/Sidenotes#sidebar-tables">Sidenotes In Web Design Â· Gwern.net</a></li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://www.gwern.net/Sidenotes#tufte-css">Tufte solution</a> (Pure CSS/HTML)</p>

    <p>Tufteâ€™s sidenotes are too difficult to access in markdown. This is the syntax required to produce a sidenote/margin note:</p>

    <p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;label for="mn-demo" class="margin-toggle"&gt;&amp;#8853;&lt;/label&gt;
&lt;input type="checkbox" id="mn-demo" class="margin-toggle"/&gt;
&lt;span class="marginnote"&gt;
This is a margin note.
&lt;/span&gt;</code></p>

    <p>this could be made easier using an include, but the syntax would still be far more cumbersome than a classic markdown footnote.</p>
